<br>
The higher level you are compared to the mob, the harder it will be for the mob to break the charm.<br>
<br>
As for magic resistance it can be lowered 20 points by using Glamour of Tunare (level 53 spell). This is a MUST when charming. Never ever charm without it.<br>
<br>
In regards to charisma I have never seen any conclusive evidence suggesting one or the other. Verant has stated that cha is more important to chanters when charming than Druids, and even for chanters cha is a very secondary skill when it comes to how long a mob stays charmed.<br>
On the other hand 56 cha is a bit on the low side, so it wouldn't hurt to boost it I guess. But if you're having a lot of problems charming, don't expect charisma to make it much better.<br>
<br>
If I were you I would just quad. <br>
The only place (pre-pop) where I could get better xp charming than quadding, was in ME (level 60 though, so you might wanna wait a few levels), until they messed up aggro in that zone. Mobs with no aggro would suddenly aggro from across the zone and beeline straight for you, dragging a horde of mobs with it.<br>
Don't even know if it was fixed as I haven't been back for quite a while.  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=463682"> Zeel Zanar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Druid of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqcompanions.com">The Companions</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sorran>Sorran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/10/03 3:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charm soloing</span><hr size=1> I am a hafling as well, so I also have the burden of low CHA (base 50). I can't say for sure whether CHA affects charm duration or not, but I can say that a low CHA has not stopped charm solo'ing becoming the only way I solo, even back in Luclin, and my CHA is at 86 in my standard gear. If I recall correctly, there are two fairly cheap jewellery items that add +10 CHA each (one is a face piece, but I can't remember the other), and a Lodizal Shell Sheild (a great item all around for almost any druid) adds another 10. Check the Bazaar for a few CHA increasing items and you should be able to get 30-40 points worth of CHA in fairly short order, giving you a set of gear you can swap in when you want to do some charming.<br>
<br>
I can't recommend becoming a skilled charm solo'er enough - in PoP its the only way to fly - stick at it =). As Zeel mentioned, ME is a great place to charm solo when you are in the 55-60 level range - it teaches you excellent crowd control (something that can come in very handy in normal xp groups as well), because of the adds you always get from traps, large aggro ranges, etc, using root and snare. By the time PoP came out, I was pulling anywhere from 6-8 mobs at once in ME and then killing them one at a time with a charmed ravenous beast while root parking the others. I was able to keep 3 entire goranga camps clear, solo =) The xp was very nice, and I got a fair few VT shards for guildies =). Before ME, you can charm solo in places like Dawnshroud Peaks, the Overthere, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
All in all, charm solo'ing is an extremely powerful skill, especially in PoP, and it lets you acquire mad xp, and its a hell of a lot more challenging and exciting than quad kiting, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
<br>
Elder Sorran<br>
Storm Warden of Elitists and Vagrants. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=witzo>witzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/10/03 11:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charm soloing</span><hr size=1> So in your experience Sorran, would you say Charisma DID effect charm duration?  Spending the PP on some charisma gear isn't an issue, as much as I wasn't sure if it would be worth swapping out mana/hp/wis gear to do so and have no effect.  At level 54 I've been mostly doing raptors for decent xp and rockhoppers in mons to support my tailoring addiction.  Is 54 too low to try charming in ME?<br>
