Also I heard PoG is good xp charm soloing.  Anyone have any experience doing so there? I'm already kos there so not worried about faction.  Mostly worried about how difficult or not would it be to do cr/rez <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sorran>Sorran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/17/03 8:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charm soloing</span><hr size=1> Long post inc =). Charming is my bag baby!<br>
<br>
In ME, there are two good charm solo spots that I found.<br>
<br>
The first one is in the open area right by the DSP zone line, between the zone wall and where the goranga's roam too, and out as far as the corner of the ruined wall (where the 3 goranga spawn is). There are two main drawbacks to this area, although one is only applicable as you get closer to level 60 and beyond. The first drawback is that you have to go a fair way out of your way to actually get a pet, which at this camp is almost always a spectral wolf (all spectral wolves are charmable with Command of Karana - their max level is 51 iirc, with a max hit of 139). These sometimes roam to the single rock a short distance directly out from the DSP zone line. If you don't want to wait for this to happen, run over to near the Akheva zone line where it much easier to find a spectral wolf. Aggro it, make sure you have him single, then charm him. Once done, run back around the zone wall to the DSP zone line area, with your pet in tow. Once you have your pet, just pull whatever goranga's catch your fancy. Use Harmony to single pull the 3 goranga scout camp (the goranga Seer can spawn at this camp) or pull without Harmony if you want to brush up on your crowd control skills. The second drawback is that 90% of the mobs in this area are under level 55 - this means that, at level 60, you don't get the xp bonus for killing something that is less than 5 levels lower than your level. Not a huge pain, but something to note nonetheless.<br>
<br>
The second spot, while it can be just as &quot;safe&quot; as the DSP area also allows for the more experienced charm solo'er to really go wild. It's the area to the immediate right of the entrance to the building which houses the Akheva zone line (assuming you are facing the building). I'd recommend moving over here once you hit level 59. Assuming you are now comfortable with controlling your pet, its time to move up to charming ravenous beasts, only some of which are charmable. You need to find one with a max hit of 149 or 151 (level 52 and 53 respectively). I found the easiest way was to charm a spectral wolf as normal, then carefully pull single ravenous wolves and just sit down and let the mob get a free &quot;max hit&quot; on you - if it was a 149 or 151, break charm on the spectral and recharm the ravenous, otherwise kill the ravenous and try again. At the Akheva spot, you want to focus on killing goranga scouts and mobs that spawn from traps - these are all level 55+ and offer the best xp. You will, however, get plenty of unwanted aggro from toilers and robes. There are 3 goranga scout camps you can pull. The first is very safe - its 2 mobs right in front of the Akheva building. The second is a little more dangerous - its 3 scouts over the hill to the left of the Akheva building. To pull this camp &quot;cleanly&quot; more easily, you should first clear the two robed mobs that flank the stairs into the Akheva building. For added safety, kill the two toilers behind them as well. Once they are gone, if you time your pull between roaming mobs, you can get the 3 goranga scouts cleanly. The final goranga camp is for advanced students only, as it involves anywhere from 6 to 10 mobs per pull. The camp is situated a ways out from the Akheva building, amongst a group of large rocks at the base of a hill. Pulling these mobs back to camp will *always* get you adds, some from traps, some roamers (toilers and robed mobs). The key is to snare everything on the way back to camp, making 100% sure you spam the &quot;pet back off&quot; key every time you get hit, until you have all mobs snared and parked around your camp. This pull is hell of a rush, and a lot of fun, but be prepared to die a few times while you get comfortable with it =). Note that the first two scout camps can spawn a named (battlemaster at the first camp, prophet at the second camp). The third scout camp (the hardest one) has two named that can spawn - forager and savant.<br>
<br>
The named goranga's can be dangerous. The battlemaster and the forager are nothing too bad - they hit hard but are straight up melee fights - no problem. However, the prophet, seer and savant are all spell casters and can gate. The seer (which spawns over at the DSP camp) is not a huge problem when he gates - he won't go far, and will rarely aggro anything else. The prophet and savant however, are another matter entirely - the prophet is doable and careful use of Fury of Air can stop the first gate attempt, long enough for your pet to finish him. The savant is, for some reason, much harder to stop gating - I think mainly because he has more hit points, so your pet has trouble finishing him off, even with a stun. I only ever managed to kill the savant once when my pet got lucky with his attacks and landed a string of near max damage hits right at the end of the fight. If a named does gate on you, its not instant death, because nothing in ME summons, but it does mean your name gets added to hate list of pretty much every mob that comes close to the named. Best option here is to simply break charm on your pet, root it, and relog - your pet should still be there (fully healed too) when you log back in.<br>
<br>
In PoN, there is one *excellent* solo spot, both for xp and pp. When you zone into PoN, follow the right hand zone wall around until you see the ravenous nightstalkers - these are all charmable with Command of Karana, and drop raw diamonds, diamonds and even blue diamonds with wonderful frequency. The nightstalkers are on a very fast spawn (like 7-8mins) so even with c3 its hard to keep the camp completely clear. If you do manage it, there are plenty of other mobs (spiders, birds, trees) that roam nearby to pull. The nightstalkers all go light blue at level 63, and the trees, birds, etc all go light blue at level 64. Note that some of the birds are low enough level to be charmable with Command of Karana (average about one in 5), but even if you find one, avoid doing it - they break charm *alot* using Command of Karana - the nightstalkers are much more reliable. If you have Command of Tunare, the birds make great pets (hit for 350 odd, compared to 288 for the nightstalkers).<br>
<br>
PoG I haven't tried yet - I want to tho, but I need to find out exactly what is charmable, and exactly what summons before I try it. CR is definitely a concern in PoG, but xp loss on death at level 65 is minimal enough that you could easily eat an unrezzed death or two and not be that badly off.<br>
<br>
If you ever have any charm questions (or druid questions in general), feel free to fire me a tell in /game as well as posting here.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
